  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Inquisitor Jaq Draco of the Ordo Malleus begins with a covert watch over a Genestealer purge and finds a deeper heresy moving inside the Imperium itself. The trail leads to the Hydra, a rogue Inquisition cabal chasing mind-slavery as salvation and dragging Draco toward the same corruption it claims to defeat. Around him gather the trilogy's strange retinue: Meh'Lindi the Callidus Assassin, Vitali Googol the Navigator, and Grimm the Squat engineer. The first Warhammer 40,000 novel reads like feverish Inquisition noir, half founding text and half early-canon hallucination.",
